              <h3>Mountain Pose (Tadasana)</h3>
              <p class="pose-sanskrit">Tada = Mountain</p>
              <div class="pose-info">
                <div class="pose-description">
                  <p>The foundation of all standing poses, Mountain Pose teaches proper alignment and establishes stability.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="pose-details">
                  <div class="pose-alignment">
                    <h4>Key Alignment</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Feet parallel, hip-width apart</li>
                      <li>Distribute weight evenly across both feet</li>
                      <li>Engage quadriceps and lift kneecaps</li>
                      <li>Lengthen tailbone toward floor</li>
                      <li>Stack shoulders over hips, ears over shoulders</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pose-benefits">
                    <h4>Benefits</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Improves posture</li>
                      <li>Strengthens thighs, knees, and ankles</li>
