        <div class="guide-content-box" id="seated-content">
          <h2>Seated Poses</h2>
          <div class="poses-description">
            <p>Seated poses improve flexibility, especially in the hips and spine, and cultivate a sense of groundedness in your practice.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="poses-grid">
            <div class="pose-card">
              <h3>Easy Pose (Sukhasana)</h3>
              <p class="pose-sanskrit">Sukha = Easy, Comfortable</p>
              <div class="pose-info">
                <div class="pose-description">
                  <p>A simple cross-legged seated position that provides a stable base for breathing and meditation practices.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="pose-details">
                  <div class="pose-alignment">
                    <h4>Key Alignment</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Sit on edge of blanket or cushion</li>
                      <li>Cross legs comfortably</li>
                      <li>Knees lower than hips if possible</li>
                      <li>Spine tall, shoulders relaxed</li>
                      <li>Hands resting on knees or in lap</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pose-benefits">
                    <h4>Benefits</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Opens hips and stretches knees</li>
                      <li>Calms mind and reduces anxiety</li>
                      <li>Strengthens back muscles</li>
                      <li>Improves posture</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pose-card">
              <h3>Staff Pose (Dandasana)</h3>
              <p class="pose-sanskrit">Danda = Staff</p>
              <div class="pose-info">
                <div class="pose-description">
                  <p>The foundation for all seated forward bends, Staff Pose teaches proper spinal alignment.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="pose-details">
                  <div class="pose-alignment">
                    <h4>Key Alignment</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Sit with legs extended forward</li>
                      <li>Flex feet, pointing toes toward ceiling</li>
                      <li>Sit bones grounded, spine tall</li>
                      <li>Hands on floor beside hips</li>
                      <li>Shoulders relaxed, chest open</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pose-benefits">
                    <h4>Benefits</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Strengthens back muscles</li>
                      <li>Improves posture</li>
                      <li>Stretches hamstrings</li>
                      <li>Prepares body for forward bends</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pose-card">
              <h3>Seated Forward Fold (Paschimottanasana)</h3>
              <p class="pose-sanskrit">Paschima = West, Back body; Uttana = Intense stretch</p>
              <div class="pose-info">
                <div class="pose-description">
                  <p>A deep forward bend that stretches the entire back of the body from heels to head.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="pose-details">
                  <div class="pose-alignment">
                    <h4>Key Alignment</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Begin in Staff Pose</li>
                      <li>Inhale to lengthen spine</li>
                      <li>Exhale to hinge at hips and fold forward</li>
                      <li>Hold shins, ankles, or feet as flexibility allows</li>
                      <li>Keep spine long rather than rounding</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pose-benefits">
                    <h4>Benefits</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Stretches hamstrings and spine</li>
                      <li>Calms nervous system</li>
                      <li>Stimulates liver and kidneys</li>
                      <li>Improves digestion</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="guide-content-box" id="backbends-content">
          <h2>Backbends</h2>
          <div class="poses-description">
            <p>Backbends open the chest and shoulders, increase spinal mobility, and counteract the effects of sitting and slouching.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="poses-grid">
            <div class="pose-card">
              <h3>Cobra Pose (Bhujangasana)</h3>
              <p class="pose-sanskrit">Bhujanga = Snake, Cobra</p>
              <div class="pose-info">
                <div class="pose-description">
                  <p>A gentle backbend that strengthens the spine and opens the chest and shoulders.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="pose-details">
                  <div class="pose-alignment">
                    <h4>Key Alignment</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Lie on belly, hands under shoulders</li>
                      <li>Elbows close to sides</li>
                      <li>Press tops of feet into floor</li>
                      <li>Engage legs and core as you lift chest</li>
                      <li>Keep shoulders away from ears</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pose-benefits">
                    <h4>Benefits</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Strengthens spine</li>
                      <li>Opens chest and shoulders</li>
                      <li>Stimulates abdominal organs</li>
                      <li>Relieves stress and fatigue</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pose-card">
              <h3>Bridge Pose (Setu Bandhasana)</h3>
              <p class="pose-sanskrit">Setu = Bridge; Bandha = Lock</p>
              <div class="pose-info">
                <div class="pose-description">
                  <p>A gentle backbend that strengthens the back, glutes, and hamstrings while opening the chest.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="pose-details">
                  <div class="pose-alignment">
                    <h4>Key Alignment</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Lie on back, knees bent, feet hip-width apart</li>
                      <li>Place feet close to buttocks</li>
                      <li>Arms alongside body, palms down</li>
                      <li>Press into feet to lift hips</li>
                      <li>Keep thighs parallel</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pose-benefits">
                    <h4>Benefits</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Strengthens back, glutes, and hamstrings</li>
                      <li>Opens chest and shoulders</li>
                      <li>Stimulates thyroid and lungs</li>
                      <li>Calms mind and reduces anxiety</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pose-card">
              <h3>Camel Pose (Ustrasana)</h3>
              <p class="pose-sanskrit">Ustra = Camel</p>
              <div class="pose-info">
                <div class="pose-description">
                  <p>A deep backbend that opens the entire front of the body while strengthening the back.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="pose-details">
                  <div class="pose-alignment">
                    <h4>Key Alignment</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Kneel with knees hip-width apart</li>
                      <li>Place hands on lower back for support</li>
                      <li>Lift chest and arch back</li>
                      <li>Reach for heels if accessible</li>
                      <li>Keep neck in neutral position</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pose-benefits">
                    <h4>Benefits</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Stretches entire front of body</li>
                      <li>Strengthens back muscles</li>
                      <li>Improves posture</li>
                      <li>Stimulates digestive and reproductive organs</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="guide-content-box" id="inversions-content">
          <h2>Inversions</h2>
          <div class="poses-description">
            <p>Inversions reverse the effects of gravity, bringing fresh blood flow to the brain and offering a new perspective both physically and mentally.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="poses-grid">
            <div class="pose-card">
              <h3>Downward-Facing Dog (Adho Mukha Svanasana)</h3>
              <p class="pose-sanskrit">Adho = Downward; Mukha = Face; Svana = Dog</p>
              <div class="pose-info">
                <div class="pose-description">
                  <p>A mild inversion that creates length in the spine while strengthening the arms and legs.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="pose-details">
                  <div class="pose-alignment">
                    <h4>Key Alignment</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Hands shoulder-width apart, fingers spread</li>
                      <li>Feet hip-width apart</li>
                      <li>Press firmly through hands</li>
                      <li>Lift hips high, creating an inverted V shape</li>
                      <li>Relax head between arms</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pose-benefits">
                    <h4>Benefits</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Stretches hamstrings, calves, and shoulders</li>
                      <li>Strengthens arms and legs</li>
                      <li>Energizes the body</li>
                      <li>Calms the mind</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pose-card">
              <h3>Legs-Up-The-Wall (Viparita Karani)</h3>
              <p class="pose-sanskrit">Viparita = Inverted; Karani = Action</p>
              <div class="pose-info">
                <div class="pose-description">
                  <p>A gentle, restorative inversion that relieves tired legs and calms the nervous system.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="pose-details">
                  <div class="pose-alignment">
                    <h4>Key Alignment</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Sit with one hip against wall</li>
                      <li>Swing legs up wall as you lie back</li>
                      <li>Buttocks close to or touching wall</li>
                      <li>Arms relaxed at sides, palms up</li>
                      <li>Close eyes and breathe deeply</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pose-benefits">
                    <h4>Benefits</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Relieves tired legs</li>
                      <li>Reduces swelling in feet and legs</li>
                      <li>Calms nervous system</li>
                      <li>Eases anxiety and insomnia</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pose-card">
              <h3>Shoulder Stand (Sarvangasana)</h3>
              <p class="pose-sanskrit">Sarva = All; Anga = Limb</p>
              <div class="pose-info">
                <div class="pose-description">
                  <p>Often called the "queen of asanas," this inversion brings numerous benefits to the entire body.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="pose-details">
                  <div class="pose-alignment">
                    <h4>Key Alignment</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Begin on back with knees bent</li>
                      <li>Lift hips and support lower back with hands</li>
                      <li>Straighten legs toward ceiling</li>
                      <li>Keep elbows shoulder-width apart</li>
                      <li>Gaze toward chest</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pose-benefits">
                    <h4>Benefits</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Stimulates thyroid and prostate glands</li>
                      <li>Improves circulation</li>
                      <li>Calms nervous system</li>
                      <li>Helps relieve insomnia</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
